{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_8","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' config/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml\"","aggregated_output":"metadata:\n  milestone_id: milestone_1\n  title: Freeze the scientific claim and the demo claim\n  status: design_locked\n  brief_version: 1.0.0\n  hypothesis_version: 1.0.0\n  last_updated: 2026-03-21\n  owners:\n    - Grant: scientific content lead\n    - Jack: repo artifact implementation\n  source_documents:\n    - path: ../response_milestone_1.md\n      role: scientific source of truth for Milestone 1\n    - path: ../fruit_fly_wave_simulation_milestones.md\n      role: ownership and deliverable requirements for Milestone 1\n\nscientific_lock:\n  locked_hypothesis: \"Morphology-resolved surface dynamics constitute an additional intraneuronal computational degree of freedom, capable of shaping circuit input-output transformations through distributed spatiotemporal state on neuronal structure.\"\n  operational_claim: \"In a connectome-constrained Drosophila visual motion circuit, adding a morphology-resolved surface state should produce small but reproducible, geometry-dependent departures in shared circuit observables relative to fair point/reduced-neuron baselines.\"\n  emphasis:\n    - detectability of a small effect\n    - distinctness of a small effect\n    - falsifiability of a small effect\n  core_observable: geometry-sensitive shared-output effect\n  primary_observable: geometry-sensitive null-direction suppression\n  companion_observables:\n    - response latency\n    - direction selectivity index\n  baseline_definitions:\n    P0: Canonical point baseline using passive leaky linear non-spiking single-compartment neurons matched to the same connectome slice and readout.\n    P1: Stronger reduced baseline using an effective-point or reduced-compartment model with explicit synaptic integration current or explicit delay structure.\n\ndecision_rule:\n  require_all: true\n  items:\n    - id: m1_nonzero_shared_output_effect\n      statement: Nonzero shared-output effect on null-direction suppression, latency, or DSI.\n    - id: m1_geometry_dependence\n      statement: Geometry dependence through topology or morphology perturbation.\n    - id: m1_survives_stronger_baseline\n      statement: Survival against the stronger reduced baseline P1.\n    - id: m1_seed_parameter_stability\n      statement: Stability across seeds and modest parameter changes.\n\nsuccess_criteria:\n  - id: m1_nonzero_shared_output_effect\n    name: Geometry-sensitive null-direction suppression effect\n    description: Detect a nonzero shared-output effect centered on null-direction suppression when morphology-bound surface dynamics are present.\n    metric:\n      name: geometry_sensitive_null_direction_suppression_effect\n      derived_from:\n        - null_direction_suppression_index\n        - geometry_sensitive_shared_output_effect\n      threshold: null\n      threshold_status: intentionally_unspecified\n    comparison: surface_wave/intact versus matched baseline/intact, with the intact-minus-baseline gap contrasted against the shuffled condition\n    expected_relationship: The surface-wave model produces a small but reproducible shared-output departure relative to the matched baseline.\n    required_conditions:\n      - same circuit\n      - same stimulus\n      - shared downstream readout\n      - intact topology present\n      - shuffled topology present\n    evidence_level: strong\n    notes: Optimize Milestone 1 around null-direction suppression rather than headline task accuracy.\n  - id: m1_latency_companion_effect\n    name: Latency companion effect\n    description: Track latency as the main mechanistic companion observable for the primary shared-output effect.\n    metric:\n      name: response_latency_to_peak_ms\n      derived_from:\n        - shared output traces\n      threshold: null\n      threshold_status: intentionally_unspecified\n    comparison: surface_wave/intact versus matched baseline/intact, then intact versus shuffled\n    expected_relationship: Latency shifts or latency gradients should align with the shared-output difference instead of contradicting it.\n    required_conditions:\n      - same circuit\n      - same stimulus\n      - paired shared-output traces\n      - intact topology present\n      - shuffled topology present\n    evidence_level: moderate\n    notes: Latency is a companion observable, not a substitute for the primary geometry-sensitive null-direction suppression effect.\n  - id: m1_geometry_dependence\n    name: Intact-versus-shuffled geometry dependence\n    description: Show that the shared-output effect materially shrinks or disappears when synapse landing geometry or topology is shuffled.\n    metric:\n      name: geometry_sensitive_shared_output_effect\n      derived_from:\n        - null_direction_suppression_index\n        - response_latency_to_peak_ms\n        - direction_selectivity_index\n      threshold: null\n      threshold_status: intentionally_unspecified\n    comparison: (surface_wave/intact - baseline/intact) versus (surface_wave/shuffled - baseline/shuffled)\n    expected_relationship: The intact condition retains a larger effect than the shuffled condition.\n    required_conditions:\n      - intact topology arm\n      - shuffled topology arm\n      - matched baseline arm\n      - matched surface-wave arm\n    evidence_level: strong\n    notes: This is the clearest falsifiability check for Milestone 1.\n  - id: m1_survives_stronger_baseline\n    name: Survival against stronger reduced baseline P1\n    description: Confirm that the shared-output effect is not explained away by a stronger reduced baseline with explicit integration current or delay structure.\n    metric:\n      name: geometry_sensitive_shared_output_effect\n      derived_from:\n        - null_direction_suppression_index\n        - response_latency_to_peak_ms\n      threshold: null\n      threshold_status: intentionally_unspecified\n    comparison: surface_wave/intact versus baseline P1/intact, with the same comparison available under shuffled topology\n    expected_relationship: The Milestone 1 effect remains detectable against P1, not only against P0.\n    required_conditions:\n      - baseline P1 arm\n      - matched surface-wave arm\n      - intact topology present\n    evidence_level: very_strong\n    notes: No numeric margin is locked yet; only the requirement that the effect survive the stronger reduced baseline.\n  - id: m1_seed_parameter_stability\n    name: Stability across seeds and modest parameter changes\n    description: Verify that the effect is not a one-seed or one-parameter accident.\n    metric:\n      name: geometry_sensitive_shared_output_effect_across_seeds\n      derived_from:\n        - geometry_sensitive_shared_output_effect\n      threshold: null\n      threshold_status: intentionally_unspecified\n    comparison: repeated runs across a small seed sweep and modest parameter perturbations\n    expected_relationship: Effect direction and qualitative interpretation remain stable across the planned seed sweep and modest parameter changes.\n    required_conditions:\n      - seed sweep\n      - modest parameter perturbation sweep\n      - same circuit\n      - same stimulus family\n    evidence_level: strong\n    notes: The source material specifies stability qualitatively and does not yet lock a numeric tolerance.\n\ndemo_story:\n  duration_seconds: 60\n  beats:\n    - id: stimulus_setup\n      seconds: 0-10\n      description: Show a simple moving edge across a small retinotopic patch.\n    - id: matched_split_view\n      seconds: 10-25\n      description: Show point baseline and surface-wave model side by side on the same T4/T5-centered circuit.\n    - id: shared_output_overlay\n      seconds: 25-38\n      description: Overlay the shared output traces and call out a small difference in null-direction suppression or latency.\n    - id: geometry_ablation\n      seconds: 38-50\n      description: Toggle intact versus shuffled synapse landing geometry and show the wave-specific difference collapse or materially shrink.\n    - id: summary_freeze\n      seconds: 50-60\n      description: Freeze on a summary panel stating Small, causal, geometry-dependent computational effect.\n\nmust_show_outputs:\n  - id: stimulus_overview\n    kind: ui_state\n    description: Simple moving-edge stimulus shown on the chosen retinotopic patch.\n    artifact_name: ui/stimulus_overview.json\n  - id: surface_vs_baseline_split_view\n    kind: ui_state\n    description: Side-by-side view of scalar baseline activity and distributed surface state for the same circuit and stimulus.\n    artifact_name: ui/surface_vs_baseline_split_view.json\n  - id: shared_output_trace_overlay\n    kind: plot\n    description: Overlay of shared output traces for the matched surface-wave and baseline conditions.\n    artifact_name: plots/shared_output_trace_overlay.png\n  - id: null_direction_suppression_comparison\n    kind: plot\n    description: Comparison plot for the primary observable centered on geometry-sensitive null-direction suppression.\n    artifact_name: plots/null_direction_suppression_comparison.png\n  - id: latency_shift_comparison\n    kind: plot\n    description: Latency companion plot aligned to the same comparison arms.\n    artifact_name: plots/latency_shift_comparison.png\n  - id: topology_ablation_comparison\n    kind: plot\n    description: Intact versus shuffled comparison showing whether the shared-output effect is geometry-dependent.\n    artifact_name: plots/topology_ablation_comparison.png\n  - id: baseline_challenge_comparison\n    kind: plot\n    description: P0 versus P1 baseline challenge plot for the same observable family.\n    artifact_name: plots/baseline_challenge_comparison.png\n  - id: milestone_decision_panel\n    kind: ui_state\n    description: Final panel summarizing the four-part Milestone 1 decision rule.\n    artifact_name: ui/milestone_decision_panel.json\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
